calculateFibonacci(uint256).details: This function sends the request to Bonsai through the on-chain relay.      The request will trigger Bonsai to run the specified RISC Zero guest program with      the given input and asynchronously return the verified results via the callback below.

fibonacci(uint256).details: The sequence is defined as 1, 1, 2, 3, 5 ... with fibonacci(0) == 1.      Only precomputed results can be returned. Call calculate_fibonacci(n) to precompute.

calculateFibonacci(uint256).notice: Sends a request to Bonsai to have have the nth Fibonacci number calculated.

constructor.notice: Initialize the contract, binding it to a specified Bonsai relay and RISC Zero guest image.

fibImageId().notice: Image ID of the only zkVM binary to accept callbacks from.

fibonacci(uint256).notice: Returns nth number in the Fibonacci sequence.

fibonacciCache(uint256).notice: Cache of the results calculated by our guest program in Bonsai.

storeResult(uint256,uint256).notice: Callback function logic for processing verified journals from Bonsai.
